  "notes": "Request body is sent URL-encoded as `jData={...}&jKey=...` (form-style), not as a raw JSON body. Both query params jData* and jKey* are mandatory; both jData fields uid* and actid* are mandatory. The cash value in the sample success response is an extremely large placeholder (\"1500000000000000.00\"). The response is segment/product-wise: seg is one of CM / FO / FX, and many fields carry segment/product suffixes — _e/_d/_f/_c for Equity/Derivative/FX/Commodity and _i/_m/_c/_h/_b for Intraday/Margin/Cash-n-Carry/High-leverage/Bracket-order. Response fields turnoverlmt and pendordvallmt are listed under \"Additional Risk Limits\" with NO description in the doc (empty Possible-value and Description cells). The \"Cash Additional Field\" daycash description spans two lines in the doc. The sample success response uses key \"urmtom\" (unrealized mtom) whereas the response-field table lists \"unmtom\" for \"Current unrealized mtom\" — an apparent name inconsistency between sample and field table (preserved verbatim in both). The doc groups response fields into sections: stat/actid/prd/seg/exch; Cash Primary; Cash Additional; Margin Utilized; Margin Used components (cbu/csc/rpnl/unmtom); a top-level margin/collateral block (marprt/span/expo/premium/varelm/grexpo/greexpo_d/scripbskmar/addscripbskmrg/brokerage/collateral/cash_coll/grcoll); Additional Risk Limits; Additional Risk Indicators; and the Margin-used detailed breakup fields (rzpnl_*/uzpnl_*/span_*/expo_*/premium_*/varelm_*/marprt_*/scripbskmar_*/addscripbskmrg_*/brkage_*/mr_*); then request_time and emsg. Field names with OCR line-wrap spaces in the raw text (e.g. \"addscripbskmrg_ d_i\", \"addscripbskmrg_f _i\") were normalized by removing the wrap spaces.",
  "confidence": "high",
